Duncan Larcombe suggested that one of the motivating factors in the Firm's decision not to release the finding of a bullying inquiry involving Meghan Markle is due to fears it could spark a war of words with the Sussexes. Meghan and Harry previously slammed the Royal Family during an interview with Oprah Winfrey. Mr Lamcombe said: “I think the reason they are not publishing any of this is because the Palace is running scared of the Duke and Duchess of Sussex. “I think they know that if they publish the report, the next thing that will happen potentially is for Harry and Meghan to play the victim and go on Oprah and cause another world of pain.” Follow below for live updates...